---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
    title="Accessibility CSS Demos"
    description="Interactive accessibility-focused CSS demos for Layered Semantic CSS."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Tool</p>

        <h1>
            Accessibility CSS demos
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            CSS architecture should protect accessibility instead of treating it
            as an afterthought.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Focus visibility
        </h2>

        <p>
            Keyboard users need clear focus states. LSCSS treats focus styling
            as a baseline requirement, not a decorative extra.
        </p>

        <div class="a11y-demo-card">
            <a class="demo-button" href="#focus-demo">
                Focusable link
            </a>

            <button class="demo-button" type="button">
                Focusable button
            </button>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Hover-only failure
        </h2>

        <p>
            Interaction states should not rely on hover alone.
        </p>

        <div class="a11y-demo-card hover-demo">
            <button class="demo-button" type="button">
                Hover or focus me
            </button>

            <p class="hint">
                This hint appears on hover and keyboard focus.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Reduced motion
        </h2>

        <p>
            Motion should respect user preferences.
        </p>

        <div class="a11y-demo-card">
            <div class="motion-demo" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Logical properties and direction
        </h2>

        <p>
            Logical properties reduce directional assumptions and help CSS work
            better across writing directions.
        </p>

        <form class="tool-panel" data-direction-demo>
            <label for="direction-select">
                Text direction
            </label>

            <select id="direction-select" class="tool-input" data-direction-select>
                <option value="ltr">Left to right</option>
                <option value="rtl">Right to left</option>
            </select>
        </form>

        <article class="logical-demo" data-logical-demo dir="ltr">
            <h3>
                Logical spacing example
            </h3>

            <p>
                This card uses logical properties instead of left and right.
            </p>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
<pre><code>.demo-button:focus-visible {
    outline: 3px solid currentColor;
    outline-offset: 0.25rem;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .motion-demo {
        animation: none;
    }
}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <script type="module" src="/scripts/accessibility-demos.js"></script>
</DocsLayout>
